Just doing some testing, looks like `ssize_t` is not implemented by the MSVC compiler as it's not C-standard, but it can be imported by:
```
//sdust.cL.9
#if defined(_MSC_VER)
#include <BaseTsd.h>
typedef SSIZE_T ssize_t;
#endif
```

Following that fix I can confirm that r794 now gives the same results on windows and linux. 

It gives different results to v2.10-r761, however, is that expected due to other changes? I haven't dug into the details of the differences.

