Re: nervousness, yes. I’m thinking that right now, 100% of our sources would come through as attribution required if we didn’t do this, which smelled funny. There are 227 sources currently with `attribution` tags defined, which would mark them as required. To be clear, this works as you’re describing:

    {
        "license": { "attribution": <true/false/null> }
    }

The implied value is for this case using the [existing, soon-to-be-deprecated tag](https://github.com/openaddresses/openaddresses/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#optional-tags):

    {
        "attribution": <string>
    }

So it’s two places the value can come from. Does this help your nervousness, or should I change something? [Here are the current tests](https://github.com/openaddresses/machine/blob/ff93b0a5a74a49881d47f109dc783772e19bcd16/openaddr/tests/conform.py#L718) for some better detail.

