There isn't a declarative way to describe dependencies but you can validate/adapt the whole structure after validating each field using `ChainOf`. It will look something like this:
```
field_schema = {
  "addressCountry": "Country",
  "addressState": "State"
}

COUNTRY_STATES = {
   ...
}

def validate_address(address):
    """Validate an address dict"""
    if address["addressState"] not in COUNTRY_STATES[address["addressCountry"]]:
        raise ValueError("Invalid state for country")
    return address

schema = valideer.ChainOf(
    field_schema, 
    valideer.AdaptBy(validate_address, ValueError)
)
```

