A simpler patch, which would at least prevent total completion breakdown when properties are present, would be:

```python
def _label(definition):
    if definition.type in ('function', 'method'):
        try:
            param_names = [param.name for param in definition.params]
        except AttributeError:
            param_names = []

        params = ', '.join(param_names)
        return '{}({})'.format(definition.name, params)

    return definition.name
```

If showing the setter name as a param is really needed, that logic could go inside the exception handler. But at least this would allow completion to work when we have defined properties.

